John was nearly nineteen when he was one day dismissed rather earlier than usual from his father's office , where he was studying the practice of the law . 
The band was playing down in the valley under the castle and when it came to the turn of the pipers , he heard their wild sounds with a stirring of the blood . 
Something distantly martial woke in him and he thought of Miss Mackenzie , whom he was to meet that day at dinner . 
He entered the billiard room , and was instantly greeted by his friend , cue in hand . 
'Nicholson , said he , 'I want you to lend me a pound or two till Monday . 
'You've come to the right shop , haven't you ? returned John . 
